envsocty3LT3 0.0.0.9000
  • Reference

Origin-destination matrix for the Hamilton CMA.

Source: R/envsocty3LT3-package.R
od_full.Rd

A table with information about trips that originated in the Hamilton CMA and concluded in the Hamilton CMA. This excludes trips that originated outside of the Hamilton CMA even if they concluded in the Hamilton CMA. Similarly, it excludes trips that originated in the Hamilton CMA but concluded outside of the Hamilton CMA. The zoning system is GTA06. This file is a portion of the system used by the Transportation Tomorrow Survey in the Greater Toronto and Hamilton Area. Origins and destinations are connected using straight line distances. The object is projected as UTM Zone 17N.

data(od_full)

Format

A simple features with 87,912 rows and 10 variables:

Origin

Unique identifier of zone of origin of trips in the GTA06 system

Destination

Unique identifier of zone of destination of trips in the GTA06 system

x_origin

X coordinate of the centroid of the zone of origin of trips

y_origin

Y coordinate of the centroid of the zone of origin of trips

x_destination

X coordinate of the centroid of the zone of destination of trips

y_destination

Y coordinate of the centroid of the zone of destination of trips

PairID

Unique identifier for origin-destination pair

Trips_work

Number of trips for work purposes between origin-destination

Trips_shop

Number of trips for shop purposes between origin-destination

geometry

Geometry column

Source

Transportation Tomorrow Survey (http://dmg.utoronto.ca/transportation-tomorrow-survey/tts-introduction)

Data Guide available (http://dmg.utoronto.ca/pdf/tts/2016/2016TTS_DataGuide.pdf)

Examples

 data(od_full)
 summary(od_full)
